---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Magic Chef Stove Repair | Southern California | Compact Apartment MCSGR";
const description = "Magic Chef stove repair across Southern California — 20\" compact apartment gas/electric, MCSGR series. ADU / condo / compact kitchens. Same-day, $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/magic-chef-stove-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Magic Chef still owned by Whirlpool or Maytag?",
    a: "Neither, despite the naming heritage. Magic Chef's current ownership is Recolo / MCA Entertainment, since the 2016 brand relaunch. The ownership history is worth understanding: Magic Chef originated as an American appliance brand in 1929; Maytag acquired Magic Chef in the 1990s; Whirlpool acquired Maytag in 2006 (which brought Magic Chef under Whirlpool briefly); Whirlpool sold Magic Chef to CNA International; CNA sold to Recolo / MCA Entertainment in 2016 for the current-era relaunch. The Magic Chef brand today operates as a value-tier specialist focused on compact-kitchen appliances — the 20-inch compact gas stove is Magic Chef's signature US product. For LA service, this means parts routing is through Recolo's US service network rather than Whirlpool factory-authorized channels. Typical parts lead time 3-7 days — honest framing vs. Bosch / Samsung mainstream-brand next-day parts."
  },
  {
    q: "What Magic Chef stove models are most common in LA?",
    a: "By volume, the MCSGR20 series 20-inch compact gas stove dominates our LA Magic Chef stove service. Magic Chef is essentially the only mainstream brand that still makes 20-inch residential gas stoves — Summit Appliance and Avanti make similar compact-kitchen products, but Magic Chef has the largest US installed base. The 20-inch width is what makes Magic Chef specifically relevant in LA: WeHo studio apartments, Downtown LA lofts, Koreatown small-footprint units, Silver Lake ADUs, Venice beach bungalows — these compact-kitchen segments where 30-inch standard stoves physically don't fit. Magic Chef also makes 24-inch budget stoves, 30-inch standard stoves, and HMFP-series portable/convertible units, but those are secondary to the 20-inch compact volume that defines Magic Chef's LA service territory."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Magic Chef gas stove burner won't light — where do we start?",
    a: "Most common Magic Chef service call. Diagnostic order: (1) spark-module ignition — electronic ignition doesn't click when you turn the burner knob; spark-module replacement $180–$280; (2) thermocouple — gas valve stays open only with knob held in, releases when knob released; thermocouple service $160–$240; (3) burner cap seating — cap not fully seated produces uneven spark contact; reseating free at diagnostic, cap replacement $80–$160 if damaged; (4) gas-valve stuck closed — rare but requires valve swap $220–$340; (5) gas supply issue — propane-vs-natural-gas configuration mismatch on rental-property installs; verification at diagnostic, orifice swap $140–$220 if conversion needed. Our techs carry Magic Chef spark-module + thermocouple parts in dispatch rotation — these are the volume service items."
  },
  {
    q: "Magic Chef 20\" compact vs Summit Appliance — which should I buy for my ADU?",
    a: "Both compete in the 20-inch compact gas stove niche; our honest field read: Magic Chef has larger US installed base and broader parts-availability, Summit Appliance has slightly higher build quality at higher price point. Magic Chef MCSGR20 retails $300-$500 new; Summit Appliance 20-inch gas stove retails $500-$800. Both deliver comparable 4-burner 20-inch footprint. For LA ADU / compact-kitchen applications where 20-inch fit is the priority: (1) Magic Chef for price-point-sensitive installs (rental-property owners, flip-and-sell scenarios, first-apartment budget); (2) Summit Appliance for quality-prioritized applications where the $200-$300 delta is acceptable. Repair economics on both run similar: 20-inch specialty parts have modest lead times across both brands; Magic Chef's larger installed base gives a slight parts-availability advantage."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Magic Chef stove is 12 years old — repair or replace?",
    a: "Value-tier repair-vs-replace math tips toward replacement at lower thresholds than premium brands. Magic Chef 20-inch compact stoves retail $300-$500 new; 24-inch and 30-inch budget stoves retail $400-$700. Rule of thumb: repair total over ~50-60% of replacement cost on a 10-plus-year Magic Chef = replacement is usually the right answer. Repairs that typically pencil out regardless of age: spark-module ($180-$280), thermocouple ($160-$240), burner cap ($80-$160), control knob ($80-$140) — all well under the 50% threshold. Repairs that often don't pencil out on 10-plus-year Magic Chef: gas valve swap ($220-$340) approaches the 50% line on 20-inch compact units; main control board on newer electronic-ignition models ($280-$400) exceeds replacement-unit cost on MCSGR20. Our techs give honest value-tier guidance — sometimes replacement is the right call."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Magic Chef stove repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Magic Chef stove bands: spark-module ignition $180–$280; thermocouple $160–$240; burner cap replacement $80–$160; control knob $80–$140; gas-valve swap $220–$340; orifice swap (propane / natural gas conversion) $140–$220; oven igniter (on combo-stove units with ovens) $180–$260; temperature sensor $140–$220; surface burner element (electric models) $160–$240; main control board (newer electronic-ignition) $280–$400. Magic Chef parts through Recolo US distribution — typical 3-7 day lead on common service items. For rental-property portfolio accounts with multiple Magic Chef units, standing rate structures reduce per-unit service cost meaningfully."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Magic Chef Stove Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Magic Chef Stove Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Magic Chef stove repair across LA — MCSGR20 20\" compact gas stoves + 24\" / 30\" budget + HMFP portable. ADU, condo, compact-kitchen specialist. Recolo / MCA Entertainment owned since 2016. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Magic Chef", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/magic-chef/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Magic Chef Stove Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Magic Chef stove service? Same-day across LA:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Magic Chef › Stove Repair</div>
    <h1>Magic Chef Stove Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Magic Chef is the value-tier compact-kitchen specialist brand — founded 1929, currently owned by Recolo / MCA Entertainment (since 2016 relaunch, NOT Whirlpool or Maytag despite historical ownership chain). Magic Chef's signature US product is the 20-inch compact gas stove (MCSGR20 series), which has essentially defined the LA compact-kitchen market for ADU installs, WeHo studio apartments, Koreatown small-footprint units, Silver Lake lofts, Venice beach bungalows, and Downtown LA lofts where 30-inch standard stoves physically don't fit. Our techs service Magic Chef across LA's compact-kitchen segment with honest value-tier pricing + repair-vs-replace transparency. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Recolo / MCA Entertainment since 2016</b> — NOT Whirlpool or Maytag current</li>
      <li><b>MCSGR20 20" compact gas stove</b> — LA ADU + compact-kitchen specialist</li>
      <li><b>Value-tier honest repair-vs-replace math</b> — transparent at MSRP crossover</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Magic Chef in LA — compact-kitchen specialist for ADU + apartment market</h2>
    <p>Magic Chef occupies a specific niche in LA's residential stove market that mass-market brands don't target. Recolo's 2016 Magic Chef relaunch focused on compact-kitchen appliances — 20-inch gas stoves, 18-inch dishwashers, small-capacity refrigerators — the segment where most mainstream brands have minimal or zero SKU coverage. For LA specifically, that compact-kitchen focus finds natural demand: WeHo studio apartments, Downtown LA loft conversions, Koreatown small-footprint apartments, Silver Lake ADUs, Echo Park backyard conversions, Venice beach bungalow kitchens, Glendale condo developments where 30-inch standard stoves don't fit the existing cabinetry cutouts.</p>
    <p>The Magic Chef MCSGR20 20-inch gas stove is effectively the default spec choice for LA ADU kitchens — California state-law expansion of ADU permitting (AB-68 and subsequent 2020+ legislation) accelerated the LA compact-kitchen market, and the MCSGR20 ships to match it. Our LA Magic Chef service concentrates in exactly these geographies: WeHo + Koreatown + DTLA central-LA apartment density, Silver Lake + Echo Park + Highland Park + Mount Washington eastside ADU installs, Venice + Marina del Rey coastal bungalows, Glendale + Burbank condo developments. Value-tier repair-vs-replace honesty differentiates our service approach from up-selling multi-brand shops.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Magic Chef stove failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Spark-module ignition fails</h3><p>Electronic spark ignition stops clicking when burner knob turns. Spark-module swap $180–$280. Most common Magic Chef service.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Thermocouple failure on gas models</h3><p>Gas valve stays open only while knob is held, releases when released. Thermocouple service $160–$240.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Burner cap seating</h3><p>Cap not fully seated = uneven spark contact + weak flame. Reseating often free at diagnostic; replacement $80–$160 if damaged.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Control knob + stem wear</h3><p>Value-tier plastic-knob wear in rental-turnover scenarios. Replacement $80–$140. Common 5-8 year service.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Propane vs natural gas orifice mismatch</h3><p>LA rental-property installs sometimes have wrong-orifice configurations. Orifice swap $140–$220.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Main control board (newer MCSGR electronic units)</h3><p>Current-generation Magic Chef with electronic ignition controls. Board swap $280–$400 when logic fault confirmed.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Magic Chef stove product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>MCSGR20 20" compact gas stove (signature)</h3><p>LA ADU + compact-kitchen specialist. 4-burner 20-inch footprint. Most-common Magic Chef install.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>24" budget stove</h3><p>Intermediate footprint for small kitchens that accommodate 24" but not 30".</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>30" standard stove</h3><p>Value-tier 30-inch stoves for mainstream kitchens prioritizing price.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>HMFP portable / convertible</h3><p>Countertop + portable configurations for temporary kitchen needs, RV applications, commercial food-prep auxiliary.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Electric surface burner models</h3><p>Coil + radiant-electric variants on non-gas configurations for all-electric kitchens.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Magic Chef cross-product family</h3><p>Compact refrigerators, 18" dishwashers, microwaves coordinate with Magic Chef compact stoves in ADU kitchens.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Magic Chef fact-accuracy — ownership + positioning clarification</h2>
    <p>Several Magic Chef facts warrant clarification given naming-heritage confusion.</p>
    <p><b>Current ownership: Recolo / MCA Entertainment (since 2016).</b> Not Whirlpool, not Maytag. The 2016 relaunch brought Magic Chef back as a standalone brand after passing through multiple corporate parents (Maytag → Whirlpool 2006 → CNA International → Recolo).</p>
    <p><b>Magic Chef ≠ Hobart-era Magic Chef stand-mixer history.</b> If customers Google "Magic Chef" and find Hobart stand-mixer lineage content, that's the older Magic Chef naming from mid-20th century appliance history. Current Magic Chef brand (Recolo / MCA) is a distinct corporate continuation focused on compact-kitchen appliances.</p>
    <p><b>20" compact gas stove is essentially Magic Chef territory in US market.</b> Summit Appliance + Avanti + a few other brands make 20-inch compact stoves, but Magic Chef has the largest US installed base. For ADU / compact-kitchen applications, Magic Chef is often the default spec.</p>
    <p><b>Parts supply chain: Recolo US distribution, 3-7 day typical lead.</b> Honest framing — NOT Bosch / Samsung / GE next-day parts economics. Value-tier parts network requires realistic service-time expectations at intake.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Magic Chef stove repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Spark-module ignition</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Most common service</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermocouple (gas)</td><td>$160 – $240</td><td>Flame-hold-open fault</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Burner cap replacement</td><td>$80 – $160</td><td>Seating / damage</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Control knob + stem</td><td>$80 – $140</td><td>5-8 year wear</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas valve swap</td><td>$220 – $340</td><td>Rare — stuck valve</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Orifice swap (propane / NG)</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Conversion / mismatch fix</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven igniter (combo units)</td><td>$180 – $260</td><td>Stove-with-oven models</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Temperature sensor</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Oven-side fault</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Surface burner element (electric)</td><td>$160 – $240</td><td>Coil / radiant replacement</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main control board (electronic-ignition)</td><td>$280 – $400</td><td>Newer MCSGR — often replace-unit threshold</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/magic-chef-oven-repair/">Magic Chef oven repair</a> · <a href="/brands/magic-chef-wall-oven-repair/">Magic Chef wall oven repair</a> · <a href="/brands/amana-stove-repair/">Amana stove repair (value-tier sibling)</a> · <a href="/price-list/stove-repair-cost/">stove repair cost guide</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LA service areas — where our Magic Chef stove calls come from</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>Central LA apartment + ADU</h4><p><a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a> · Koreatown · Hollywood · <a href="/downtown/">Downtown LA</a></p></div>
      <div><h4>Eastside design + ADU density</h4><p>Silver Lake · Echo Park · Highland Park · Mount Washington · Atwater Village</p></div>
      <div><h4>Coastal compact kitchens</h4><p>Venice · Marina del Rey · Santa Monica · Manhattan Beach</p></div>
      <div><h4>Glendale + Burbank condo</h4><p>Glendale · Burbank · Studio City small-footprint condos</p></div>
      <div><h4>Valley compact rentals</h4><p>Van Nuys · North Hollywood · <a href="/encino/">Encino</a></p></div>
      <div><h4>Ventura + Orange County compact</h4><p><a href="/thousand-oaks/">Thousand Oaks</a> · <a href="/irvine/">Irvine</a> · Anaheim</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Magic Chef and compact-kitchen pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/magic-chef-oven-repair/">Magic Chef oven repair →</a></li>
